-- Honduras to Appoint New Managers for Phone Provider Hondutel
-- B y   E r i c   S a b o
-- 2013-02-04T17:14:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-04/honduras-to-appoint-new-managers-for-phone-provider-hondutel.html
Honduras plans to appoint new
management to run the country’s state telecommunications
company, known as  Hondutel , over the next 120 days.  President Porfirio Lobo said the government will name the
managers today to “expand and modernize” phone services,
according to an e-emailed statement from the president’s office
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Sabo in Panama at 
